library(gapminder)
library(dplyr)

#PRIMERA PARTE

dataset_results <- read.csv("primary_results.csv")
dataset_results

#SEGUNDA PARTE

dataset_results %>% 
  filter(candidate == "Donald Trump" | candidate == "Hillary Clinton")

dataset_results %>%
  filter(party == "Democrat" & county == "Shelby")
dataset_results %>%
  filter(state == "Alabama" & votes > 15000)

#TERCERA PARTE

dataset_results %>%
  filter(state == "Texas" & county == "Denton") %>%
  select(5:7) %>%
  arrange(desc(votes))

#CUARTA PARTE Filtrar por el partido Republicano, que el candidato sea Ted Cruz en el estado de Alaska, luego agregue una columna que se llame vote_count que sea la divisin de votes por fraction_votes (votes/fraction_votes), finalmente ordene de forma descendente por vote_count.

dataset_results %>%
  filter(party == "Republican" & candidate == "Ted Cruz" & state == "Alaska")
  mutate(dataset_results, vote_count = votes/fraction_votes) %>%
  arrange(desc(vote_count))
